Dogs under 30 pounds are allowed.

description: For sale: $119,000. This loft has the best panoramic city views with three huge 8' tall south facing windows that flood the space with natural light. One block to Lunds Grocery, Many Restaurants, Brewery, Light Rail and Highways.

description:
For sale: $124,000. If you would like a virtual tour or look in person, please contact me, I am the agent and owner. Jason Huneke .

This Loft is the perfect Urban Dwelling - The 95 Walker score (Walkers paradise) building is on the Capital City Bike Path, a block from countless restaurants, breweries, skyway, light rail station. The building has a fitness room, shared laundry, one parking spot and storage locker comes with the unit.  Exposed ductwork, brick and original hardwood floors are full of character.  11' ceilings with 8' south facing windows have great views and flood the unit with natural light all year.  The unit is secluded from neighboring units, thick brick walls surround you to create a private nook with direct access to the side entrance.

description: For sale: $205,000. Enjoy urban living located in the heart of downtown St. Paul where you can walk to events, venue's, the light rail and the grocery store. This unit boasts an updated industrial feel with 12' ceilings and 8' windows overlooking the soon to be renovated Pedro Park.  The kitchen is updated, the cement floors are polished, there's a full bath and laundry is free on every level.  You'll also note plenty of storage with a walk in closet and above the bath.  Amenities include 1000 MBPS fiber optic internet, outdoor patio & grill space and a community room that can be rented.  Onsite parking is available for a fee.

description: For sale: $750,000. PLEASE WEAR MASKS AND GLOVES WHILE ON PREMISE----Incredible premiere South East Corner Penthouse at The Great Northern Lofts!  Large Master, and guest bedroom or office.  Private staircase leads you to a large private rooftop patio overlooking the Mississippi River Valley and Lowertown of Saint Paul!  Tall ceilings with ability to expand and open floor plan with original details make this an incredible home! 2 owned parking stalls (211&212).  Vacant and easy to show.     -See VIDEO-        James J. Hill would totally approve!

For sale: $115,000. Hard Wood Floors, North West facing windows plus Defused Skylight.
1100Sqft in a Creative Community. Open floor plan with 2nd Floor.

  Lowertown Lofts Artists Cooperative (LLAC) is a live/work limited equity residential cooperative - We are 29 member/owner artists, who together own the top three floors of our historic building at 255 Kellogg Boulevard East in Saint Paul's historic arts district. We are not an apartment building, rental property, or condominium association, but an affordable homeownership option. 

  Take a thorough look at our website at www.lowertownlofts.org and click on 'Live Here' to find out more about buying a share in, and becoming a working member/owner of an active housing cooperative, and whether it is the right home ownership option for you as a creative.

- You can complete our application form online: https://www.lowertownlofts.org/application-process

- Email lowertownloftscoop@gmail.com with any questions and for more information 

Financing info: https://mn.hb101.org/a/6/

-This is not a rental.
-This is not a condo.
-This is a Live/Workspace to own within a coop for creatives with a lower cost of living. No, you do not have to be an artist, but you do have to Homestead. 

-Available Share for 1/29th Share of the Cooperatives Building is $29,090 as of 4/13/2020 GOES UP $24 PER MONTH.

-Buy-in, Monthly Carrying Charge AKA. MCC: 813$ mo. covers: Wifi, Laundry,  Water, Heat, Garbage, Taxes, and Common areas. 

Also for Sale with the Share of the Coop.
Newer Stove/Fridge $1200  Free Newer Microwave With Purchase.
Member Application: https://www.lowertownlofts.org/our-building.
Solid Hardwood Desk $Negtaited prob Free to the next person.

4/13/2020 Purchase total w/Newer Stove, Fridge, Microwave, Kitchen Island, Pot/Pan Hanger & Hardwood Desk  $30290

Member Application to get in line: https://www.lowertownlofts.org/our-building.
Questions: lowertownloftscoop@gmail.com

For sale: $225,000. This updated condo in the heart of Downtown St Paul features an open and updated kitchen with granite countertops & stainless appliances. Additional updates include: Stylish light fixtures,a glass backsplash, beautiful flooring, and trim. Just 1 block to Lunds & Byerly's and convenient to the light rail. Restaurants, coffee shops, and Mears Park are all within blocks of this prime location! Enjoy downtown living at its fullest and to top it off...the views from your own private balcony are absolutely incredible!  Building amenities include: free guest parking, a guest suite, pool, sauna, fitness center, party room, rooftop tennis court, and sport court. Storage Locker dimensions 5x3.5. Welcome home!

For sale: $148,900. Breathtaking views from the 32nd floor of The Pointe!  This studio features an impeccable use of space with a custom built in desk and Murphy bed that will stay in the unit. Plenty of in unit storage and a huge walk in closet!  Must see to truly appreciate.  Conveniently located next to experience ALL that downtown has to offer: Green Line, Lund's, bars, restaurants, theaters, CHS Field and the Xcel Energy Center. Top notch amenities include: on site management, pool, hot tub, sauna, sport court, fitness center, tennis court, free visitor parking, secure package room, dry cleaning pickup, spacious party room and a guest suite.

For sale: $109,900. Great layout and sweeping views with this spacious Studio at City Walk Condominiums!  Unique floor plan offers separate spaces.  Built-in Murphy bed creates additional space.  The seller chooses to use his own bed instead of the Murphy.  Very clean, great views and connected to the skyway!  Free laundry room is right next door.  Party Room, Exercise Room and Deck/Outdoor pool are located on the 12th floor.  Parking is extra; seller currently rents a spot for $125/month.

description: For sale: $585,000. Historic Building - Remarkable Loft! Stunning condominium boasts over two thousand square feet, large arched windows, high barrel-style vaulted ceiling unique to The Great Northern, in the original workplace of Railroad Baron James J. Hill. Master suite with courtyard windows, private bath with steam shower and spacious walk-in closet. Beautifully updated kitchen and dining area. Floor to ceiling cabinetry provides ample storage and pantry space. Open concept great room features custom built bookcases with library ladder. Second bedroom/office includes Murphy bed, office desk and cabinets, and walk-in closet. Unit has two baths and new stacked washer and dryer. Close to everything downtown, the Mississippi River, Farmer's Market, and CHS Field. Many amenities. Green Line and Union Depot are only one block away. Two parking spaces (one with new electric charging plug) will transfer with the unit. Guest parking available. Shared exercise gym, community room and central courtyard.

description: For sale: $148,700. THE BEST OF AFFORDABLE LIVING! Security building  in downtown St.Paul close to groceries, restaurants and events. Connected to the Skyway system, City Walk offers an exercise room with sauna and hot tub, an outdoor salt swimming pool on a spacious deck, library, plus a party room for entertaining. Free laundry room on each floor. This light and airy, one bedroom unit has been freshly updated with new paint. Redone kitchen with newer lighting, granite counters, kitchen cabinets and fixtures. Inviting views from the 14th floor patio doors out to a 15'x5' balcony. Property includes covered parking spot and storage unit.

For sale: $339,000. Best location in downtown! Close to everything. Wonderful unit at River Park Lofts. Great functional  open floor plan for the living area. The open kitchen features high-end finishes and appliances. Large bedroom with  custom-fitted closet. Beautifully updated bath with full-size washer & dryer. Big private deck with intriguing urban cityscape view. 10x10 private storage room on ground level. 2 underground heated parking spaces.Building is skyway-connected, features exercise and community rooms,  has on-site management and is located near parks, restaurants, CHS field and light rail.

description:
For sale: $670,000. Contemporary living with traditional touches characterizes this 2,400 square foot downtown Saint Paul south facing
condominium. The bright, open spaces offer expansive views of the Mississippi River valley from the kitchen, living room and
master bedroom. There is a generous sized dining room for more formal entertaining. This home features an updated kitchen,
master bath, guest bath and wet bar area. At the opposite end of the home you will find a family room and office/hobby room.
Three underground parking spaces come with the property. Enjoy the Saint Paul Farmers' Market in the summer months or
walk to the CHS Stadium and attend a Saint Paul Saints game. Many great restaurants within walking distance year-round and
just steps to the light rail.

description: For sale: $229,900. Most charming floor plan at the Pointe. Sunny, west-facing condo, with great balcony views of steeples and historic Downtown St. Paul architecture. See the views as soon as you walk in the door! Opened-up kitchen, white quartz counters, new contemporary sliding mirrored closet doors. New custom walk-in closet system from the Container Store.  Two bedrooms + 1 Full Bath and Laundry with washer/dryer in the unit. (1/2 bath changed to laundry+sink) Linen closet. The Pointe has the most amenities of any condo building downtown: Free guest parking and on-site, helpful staff. Security cameras. Beautiful renovated guest suite ($75/night). Indoor pool. Sauna.Whirlpool. Workout room. Beautiful community room with fireplace.Grilling patio. Tennis. Grocery store and light rail stop are only ONE block away!  Dues include heat, AC, water, trash. description:
Recently sold: $339,900. Gorgeous Lowertown condo! Call Katie at 651-242-0302 to look at it today! 2.7% buyers agent commission fee! This recently renovated condo is located in the fabulous historical Great Northern Lofts building. The condo has high end amenities like stainless steel appliances, large windows, hardwood flooring, and granite counter tops. Each bedroom is on the opposite side of the condo with custom designed walk in closets (1 with hidden bookshelf door!), and its own bathroom with heated floors. Fully integrated smart home and living room/master shares a fireplace! The building is equipped with a full gym, event room, secure access, courtyard with grill, is located across the street from the Farmers Market and Saints stadium. The unit includes 2 parking spaces in the enclosed secure parking ramp and a 10x10 secure storage locker. Located in the heart of lower town walking distance to great restaurant's, nightlife, dog park and right around the corner from the Mississippi river!

The following is all recent improvements throughout!
2 sided bio ethanol fireplace with one way mirror glass and Cherry underlit mantle.
Refinished hardwood floors,
Granite countertops and under mount sink.
Refinished cabinets and under cabinet lighting
New tile backsplash. Entire unit repainted,
Retiled both bathrooms and showers
Heated bathroom floors. Hidden cherry bookcase walk in closet and Built in cabinets in both walk in closets. Rolling library ladder to storage above closet. Built in office cabinet in second bedroom and built in Murphy bed
Remote power blackout shades, High end fixtures in both bathrooms and kitchen. Cabinet microwave and Induction oven/cooktop.

description: Recently sold: $450,000. Complete re-design of this stunning Great Northern Loft. 14-foot barrel vault ceilings. Sun-filled, with 9 Paladian windows and SW orientation. Complete renovation, with superb attention to details. New foyer with french doors. Bronze hardware throughout. 3/4" oak hand-scraped floors. Full gourmet kitchen: custom crafted cabinets+new walk-in pantry+36"Bosch induction range with roll-down vent. Glass shelves with LED+island with multi-outlets and heavy-duty sliding shelves+breakfast nook w built-in storage+beverage bar+ Rohl polished nickel faucets+prep sink. Reverse osmosis water system.  2 new Baths (incl walk-in shower). 53" Troy chandelier. Wood plantation shutters. Upgraded electric/plumbing. Large walk-in master closet. 2 owned garage stalls + free guest parking.Owned storage. Workout Room.  Bike storage. Community Courtyard and Gathering Room. Assn. dues include Heat+AC+Internet. One blk from the Farmer's Market. 1450 sq ft is CAD-verified.

Recently sold: $206,975. Rossmor Loft Living in Lowertown! Industrial feel open concept design with a wall of 8 ft tall windows, 12 ft ceilings and concrete floors. Unit features 1 full bath, kitchen, large walk-in closet. View to Pedro Dog Park. Located near Lunds grocery and walking distance to light rail, farmers market, CHS Field, Mears Park and restaurants. Laundry on each floor. Parking and storage available.

description: Recently sold: $110,000. Urban studio in a great Downtown St. Paul building. Low association dues but many amenities. One block to light rail, and one block to Lunds and Pedro park. Close to restaurants and the skyway. 1207 is a Studio, with two spacious closets in the entry (sometimes the larger closet has been converted into a small office). The Pointe of St Paul has free guest parking, and an indoor pool with beautiful windows overlooking the street. The building also has a sauna, whirlpool, tennis court, grilling patio and an inviting community room. Guest suite. Free wi-fi in many of the common areas.  Possible to rent a garage stall in the building. On-site management and on-site security.  Well-staffed and maintained. Pets OK with restrictions.

Conveniently located to experience ALL that downtown has to offer: Green Line, Lund's, bars, restaurants, theaters, CHS Field and the Xcel Energy Center. description: Recently sold: $256,000. Stunning 6th floor corner loft with 12-foot ceilings boasts 270 degree views: the State Capitol to the north, the sunrise and river bluffs to the east, and Lowertown/Downtown St. Paul to the south. This is one of the few units at the Rossmor with a separate bedroom and washer/dryer. An extra large silestone kitchen island makes cooking in this spacious loft fun and easy.  The kitchen was just redone with new cabinets/silestone countertops and Bosch appliances.  The corner sink is hand hammered copper and there is a garbage disposal. The bathroom has been updated with new granite counter and a modern shower.

description: For sale: $585,000. Historic Building - Remarkable Loft! Stunning condominium boasts over two thousand square feet, large arched windows, high barrel-style vaulted ceiling unique to The Great Northern, in the original workplace of Railroad Baron James J. Hill. Master suite with courtyard windows, private bath with steam shower and spacious walk-in closet. Beautifully updated kitchen and dining area. Floor to ceiling cabinetry provides ample storage and pantry space. Open concept great room features custom built bookcases with library ladder. Second bedroom/office includes Murphy bed, office desk and cabinets, and walk-in closet. Unit has two baths and new stacked washer and dryer. Close to everything downtown, the Mississippi River, Farmer's Market, and CHS Field. Many amenities. Green Line and Union Depot are only one block away. Two parking spaces (one with new electric charging plug) will transfer with the unit. Guest parking available. Shared exercise gym, community room and central courtyard.

description:
Recently sold: $167,500. Available 2/1/20. This 1 BR loft is available in historic Market House Condo Association. This building is located directly across the street from CHS Field and the St. Paul Farmer's Market. Enjoy access to Octo Fish Bar, Salty Tart Bakery, Birch's Lowertown Brewery, Petersen's Butcher Shop and Almanac Seafood Shop all without leaving the building. All utilities are included in rent with the exception of electricity and internet. Large windows provide plenty of light, 14ft ceilings display natural beams and brick. Large storage space under bedroom (~15 ft. X 15ft X 4 ft). All stainless steel appliances. All tenants have access to shared rooftop deck and party room. Nearby parking available starting at $50/month. Building is located three blocks from the Union Station transit hub and lightrail terminal, as well as plenty of dining/nightlife options. Cats are allowed. Proof of income required during application process.

All utilities except electricity and internet included. Lease term is 12 months with option to renew.

description: Recently sold: $150,000.

Recently sold: $610,000. Absolutely breathtaking unit on the 6th floor at the much desired Great Northern Lofts. This unit boasts a stunning gourmet kit w/granite counters, cherry cabinets & stainless steel appliances. This elegant space is perfect for entertaining- open floor plan, spacious family room & tons of light! Rooftop deck access w/panoramic views of the city & the river. 2 assigned parking spots on 3rd level, close enough to start your car in the comfort of your living room. Welcome home!

Recently sold: $290,000. Are you looking for that unique upscale loft living, then come to Lowertown and check out this 9th Street Lofts gem.  This is a rare 2 story condo that has views over the common area lawn and gardens.  You will forget you are downtown looking out the massively large windows.  

The options for how you layout your furnishings is endless.  Enjoy it in it's current layout with the lower level bedroom and large main floor entertaining area.  This unit can also easily be turned into a 2 bedroom condo while keeping the bonus den area.  Plenty of room to bring the bedroom up to the main floor if you want a lower level family room...so many options to make this your perfect condo.

This unit comes with 2 parking stalls in the attached garage.  These parking stalls are the only one in the building to have a car charger, seller installed it when the building was being built.  This is a highly desirable asset as it is not an option for most garage stalls.  Perfect for anyone with an electric car.

Well cared for building with elevator access to all levels.  Make sure to check out the roof top common area patio.  The side yard between 9th Street Lofts and the church is common area for the residents of 9th Street Lofts.  Imagine having your own yard space and lawn while living in downtown. description:
Recently sold: $159,900. Not all lofts in the Rossmor were created equally! There may be slightly larger lofts in the Rossmor selling for a little less but none have a better view or a more perfect layout than this one, #618!
This unit is tucked away in a quiet, private hallway off the beaten path and away from foot traffic to and from either of the building's two elevators. 
You'll love the abundance of bright sunshine, the sky high 12 foot ceilings with a northern view for miles through wall to wall 9ft tall windows and a crystal clear panoramic view of the State Capitol! You'll buy this loft for it's stunning views...and everything else is just a beautiful bonus!
The spacious kitchen has stainless steel appliances with plenty of cabinet and counter space + center island that doubles as a breakfast bar with wine rack!
This unit is equipped with a custom built Murphy Bed enclosure so you can sleep tight at night and then tuck your bed away during the day. 
#618 is one of the rare lofts with laundry plumbing right inside the unit. There is also free laundry on every floor at the Rossmor!
Utilize the additional 100 square feet of storage space above the bathroom! 
With one of the lowest HOA fees in the building at $287/mo you can spend all that extra money you save every month on any number of 
The Rossmor building is filled with fun and friendly neighbors and is surrounded by the best Pizza, Thai, and American restaurants that Saint Paul has to offer! Plus, Tin Whiskers Brewery, a local Saint Paul Taproom, is just an elevator ride away! Love to cook? Grocery shopping for fresh fruits and vegetables is a breeze with Lunds and Byerly's located across the street. 
Love your pets? Great, so does everyone else at the Rossmor as it's the pet friendliest building in Saint Paul. 
Restaurants inside the Rossmor include: Key's Cafe & Bakery, Sawatdee Thai, and Black Sheep Coal Fired Pizza. 
Catch the light rail to US Bank Stadium, Target Field, Minneapolis, Mall Of America & more...it's just a two blocks walk from the Rossmor. 
Stream your favorite Netflix shows in true HD because Comcast provides blazing fast internet with download speeds that surpass 100mbps!

Recently sold: $267,775. Classy "Printer's Row" loft-style condo with 10' ceilings, polished concrete floors, and exposed ductwork. This unit has both a private entrance from the street, and a secured entrance through the heated parking garage. The unit also boasts cherry kitchen cabinets, custom island w/granite countertop, premium Stainless Steel appliances, and in-unit laundry. Blocks from the Light Rail, breweries, restaurants, Farmers Market, and new Saints Stadium. Watch the Virtual Tour!
